SIMPLE: pungent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pungent
<hw>Pun"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pungens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>pungere</ets>,
<ets>punctum</ets>, to prick. Cf. <er>Compunction</er>,
<er>Expunge</er>, <er>Poignant</er>, <er>Point</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
<er>Puncheon</er>, <er>Punctilio</er>, <er>Punt</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Causing a sharp sensation, as of the
taste, smell, or feelings; pricking; biting; acrid; <as>as, a
<ex>pungent</ex> spice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pungent</qex> radish biting infant's tongue.</q>
<rj><qau>Shenstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>pungent</qex> grains of titillating dust.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sharply painful; penetrating; poignant; severe;
caustic; stinging.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>pungent</qex> pains on every side.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>pungent</qex> pen played its part in rousing the
nation.</q> <rj><qau>J. R. Green.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Prickly-pointed; hard and
sharp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Acrid; piercing; sharp; penetrating; acute; keen;
acrimonious; biting; stinging.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pungently</ent>⟦br⟧
